<a href="{{ site.url }}/bible-studies-viet/Ro-ma/"><em>(<u>Bấm vào đây để đọc tiếng Việt</u>)</em></a></span>
</h4>
<ul class="toc__menu" id="markdown-toc">
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-01-v01-16/"><u>Romans 1:1-16</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Paul was called to be an apostle. The promised gospel. The obedience of faith. Paul's debt. Not ashamed of the gospel.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-01-v17-32/"><u>Romans 1:17-32</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Living by faith. Condemnation of the unrighteous.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-02-v1-11/"><u>Romans 2:1-11</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">You must also judge yourself. Hypocrisy. God’s kindness leads to repentance. The law 101.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-02-v12-29/"><u>Romans 2:12-29</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Gentile sinners. Don't just hear, do. A false sense of righteousness. Law 101.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-03-v01-09/"><u>Romans 3:1-9</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Israel as God’s channel of peace. I’m speaking in human terms. All under sin.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-03-v10-31/"><u>Romans 3:10-31</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">No one righteous. Every mouth silenced. Justified freely apart from the law. Where, then, is boasting? We uphold the law.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-04-v01-05/"><u>Romans 4:1-5</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">According to the flesh. Law & boasting. It’s enough to believe. Grace vs. works.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-04-v05-13/"><u>Romans 4:5-13</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Declaring the ungodly righteous. True blessing. Blessing apart from the law. Father of all those who believe.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-04-v14-15/"><u>Romans 4:14-15</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Law, faith, and promise. Law, wrath, and transgression.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-04-v16-18/"><u>Romans 4:16-18</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Certainty of the promise. To make the dead alive. Abraham’s faith.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-04-v19-24/"><u>Romans 4:19-24</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Who do you have faith in? Righteousness based on faith. For everyone who believes.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-04-v25-ch05-v05/"><u>Romans 4:25-5:5</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Why did Christ die? The hope of God’s glory. From sufering to hope. True hope.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-05-v05-10/"><u>Romans 5:5-10</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Why the Spirit was given. While we were still sinners.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-05-v11-21/"><u>Romans 5:11-21</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">By one man. Law and transgression.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-06-v01-11/"><u>Romans 6:1-11</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Remain in sin so that grace may increase? Died to sin. Buried with Christ. No longer enslaved to sin. Death leads to life. Once for all.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-06-v12-14/"><u>Romans 6:12-14</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Do not let sin reign. You are not under law. The truth will set you free.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-06-v15-23/"><u>Romans 6:15-23</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Shall we sin? You are slaves of the one you obey. Present your members. Those things. Freedom from sin. The wages of sin.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-07-v01-06/"><u>Romans 7:1-6</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">As long as he lives. If her husband dies. You also died to the law. Sins aroused by the law. The new law: life of the Spirit.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-07-v07-25/"><u>Romans 7:7-25</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">The role of the law. Misuse of the law. Nothing good lives in me. Who will rescue me?</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-08-v01-08/"><u>Romans 8:1-8</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">No condemnation. The law weakened by the flesh. Flesh vs. Spirit.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-08-v09-13/"><u>Romans 8:9-13</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">In the flesh. Your body is dead. To whom do you owe your obligations?</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-08-v14-23/"><u>Romans 8:14-23</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Led by the Spirit. Spirit of slavery vs. adoption. The Spirit’s voice. Suffering with Christ. Present suffering.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-08-v24-39/"><u>Romans 8:24-39</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">Hope for what we do not see. Inexpressible groanings. All things work together. If God is for us.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-09-v01-08/"><u>Romans 9:1-8</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">God’s special people. Children of promise.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-09-v09-29/"><u>Romans 9:9-29</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">God’s calling vs human efforts. God’s sovereignty. My thoughts are not your thoughts.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-09-v30-10-21/"><u>Romans 9:30-10:21</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">The two kinds of righteousness. Zeal that is based on the truth. Salvation is near. A disobedient people.</span></li>
  <li><a href="{{ site.url }}/romans/Romans-11-v01-12-02/"><u>Romans 11:1-12:2</u></a><span style="font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em;">A remnant chosen by grace. Grace vs. works. God's mercy to all. A holy and living sacrifice.</span></li>
</ul>
